    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Small bagpipes of France, especially those of aristocratic design which achieved popularity among the French nobility in the 17th and early 18th centuries.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000030041/Sadie, New Grove Dictionary of Musical Instruments (1984)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pequeñas gaitas francesas, especialmente aquellas de diseño aristocrático que lograron popularidad entre la nobleza francesa en el siglo XVII y principios del siglo XVIII.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
